<p>I want to be able to specify an HTML template for my Google Chart tooltips, instead of adding HTML directly to my data. I have a massive amount of data that I query from my MongoDB, so I want to avoid any form of data manipulation on the front-end. I also don't want to add HTML into the data on the back-end.</p>  <p>To give you an example:</p>  <p>This is a mockup of what I currently have:</p>  <pre><code>var data = new google.visualization.DataTable(); data.addColumn('number', 'Time'); data.addColumn('number', 'Available'); data.addColumn({type: 'string',role:'tooltip',                 p: {                    html:true                }});  data.addRows([ [0, 2,'&lt;b&gt;test1&lt;/b&gt;'], [15, 3,'&lt;b&gt;test2&lt;/b&gt;'] </code></pre>  <p>]); This is what I want to achieve:</p>  <pre><code>var data = new google.visualization.DataTable(); data.addColumn('number', 'Time'); data.addColumn('number', 'Available'); data.addColumn({type: 'string',role:'tooltip',                 p: {                    html:true,                     template:"&lt;b&gt;{{data}}&lt;/b&gt;"                }});  data.addRows([ [0, 2,'test1'], [15, 3,'test2'] </code></pre>  <p>]);</p>